description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’re looking for an exceptional Band 6 Physiotherapist to join our Integrated Therapy Partnership (ITP) Team. Providing a high quality, patient-centred and innovative service, this role involves assisting the team with the treatment of patients with a wide range of MSK conditions. We provide comprehensive in-service training as well as peer supervision and dedicated problem solving slots.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ITP is a partnership between Norfolk Community Health and Care NHS Trust (NCH&amp;C), Allied Health Professionals Suffolk, and Global Diagnostics. The ITP clinical team comprises Orthopaedic Clinical Specialists, Physiotherapists, Occupational Therapists and Technical Instructors. We also provide First Contact Practitioners from within our overall MSK structure. We work out of various venues, including; health centres; GP surgeries; community hospitals; and leisure centres. During the pandemic we have also been undertaking telephone, video and face to face consultations.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible hours are an option for this role. Weekend and evening working is required. Work bases will vary on need across the Norwich, South and West Norfolk localities. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We look forward to meeting you at interview.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apply now to join an organisation that has been awarded an ‘Outstanding’ rating by the Care Quality Commission (CQC), the highest possible rating and the first stand-alone NHS community trust in the country to be awarded the title.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jayson Elkins - Clinical Manager, 07919543709, jayson.elkins@nchc.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Toni Sturgeon - Clinical Manager, 07769877338&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
